Pacific
-------
[4] Philippines (Maguindanao)
Date: Thu 4 Sep 2014
Source: ABS-CBN News Central Mindanao [edited]
http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/regions/09/04/14/big-jump-measles-cases-maguindanao


The Integrated Provincial Health Office (IPHO) Maguindanao recorded 519 measles cases from January up to 27 Aug 2014. According to health officer Dr Tahir Sulaik, there were only around 100 cases during the same period last year [2013]. The town of Datu Odin Sinsuat had the most cases at 105. This is followed by Shariff Aguak with 81 cases, Parang with 57 cases, and Sultan Kudarat with 34 cases. Sulaik said some of the residents of these towns believe that measles is merely a part of a child's growth.

These towns are also densely populated, causing the disease to spread faster. IPHO has also recorded 9 deaths due to measles complications since January [2014]. Sulaik added that they did not fail in reminding parents to bring their children to health centers for immunization or to avail themselves of the vaccination given by evaluators in different barangays (districts) in Maguindanao. However, there are still some who refuse to do so.

IPHO-Maguindanao launched its measles and polio vaccination campaign at Datu Salibo town on Wednesday [3 Sep 2014], where all of the 17 barangays were submerged in flooding due to the bad weather prevailing in Mindanao.

[byline: Lore Mae Andong]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
